            <div id="id1" style="height: 43px; left: 20px; position: absolute; top: 20px; width: 515px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content Normal_External_515_43" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="Normal">
                  <p style="padding-bottom: 0pt; padding-top: 0pt; " class="Header">Autocallable</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div style="margin-left: 0px; position: relative; width: 1100px; z-index: 5; " id="body_layer">
            <div style="height: 0px; line-height: 0px; " class="bumper"> </div>
            <div id="id2" style="height: 470px; left: 32px; position: absolute; top: 33px; width: 938px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_1 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_938_470" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <p style="padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style">This tutorial is based on the usage of Autocallable pricer available freely on the site. There is no down and in put attached but the analysis can easily be extended with DIP attached. The structure payoff is as follows<br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style"><br /></p>
                  <ol>
                    <li style="line-height: 20px; padding-left: 15px; text-indent: -15px; " class="full-width" value="1">
                      <p style="text-indent: -15px; " class="paragraph_style_1"><span style="font-size: 14px; " class="Bullet">1.</span><span style="width: 4px; " class="inline-block"></span>Payoff a coupon 52$ (absolute) if the Index &gt; 110 on 1 Year from Inception and wind up<br /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li style="line-height: 20px; padding-left: 15px; text-indent: -15px; " class="full-width" value="2">
                      <p style="text-indent: -15px; " class="paragraph_style_1"><span style="font-size: 14px; " class="Bullet">2.</span><span style="width: 4px; " class="inline-block"></span>Payoff a coupon 57$ (absolute) if the Index &gt; 110 on 2 Year from Inception<br /></p>
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                  <p class="paragraph_style">If condition 1 is struck then structure gets Autocalled without 2nd condition being checked. Other extensions may simply add more payoffs for different maturities. <br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style"><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style">Let’s set the notation for this tutorial<br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style">Structure started at 9-Jan-2011, and in 1 year (or first fixing date) it will be 9-Jan-2012<br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style">Second fixing date similarly will be 9-Jan-2013<br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style"><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style">To understand or break apart any complicated structure try to picture the payoff’s intuitively. A crude way is <br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style"><br /></p>
                  <ol>
                    <li style="line-height: 20px; padding-left: 15px; text-indent: -15px; " class="full-width" value="1">
                      <p style="text-indent: -15px; " class="paragraph_style_1"><span style="font-size: 14px; " class="Bullet">1.</span><span style="width: 4px; " class="inline-block"></span>1 day before 1 year fixing date or on 8th January 2012 spot is at 109. If spot moves &gt; 1 then structure is in the money, otherwise 0. Delta will be around 26 (approximately). Delta = (52-0)/(111-109) or approx 26<br /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li style="line-height: 20px; padding-left: 15px; text-indent: -15px; " class="full-width" value="2">
                      <p style="text-indent: -15px; " class="paragraph_style_1"><span style="font-size: 14px; " class="Bullet">2.</span><span style="width: 4px; " class="inline-block"></span>Since delta is positive value above 110 and 0 before 110, gamma will change sign. Delta around 108 - 109 level is increasing but at 110 trader needs to sell the stock to fulfill the liability. If there is time remaining the delta won’t exactly be 0 above 110, but will decrease drastically above 110. Below 110 or around 105 levels there needs to be accumulation of stock. Due to both increase and decrease of delta, we notice a sign change in gamma. <br /></p>
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_2">So we are Long gamma below barrier and Short gamma above the barrier<br /></p>
                  <ol>
                    <li style="line-height: 20px; padding-left: 15px; text-indent: -15px; " class="full-width" value="3">
                      <p style="text-indent: -15px; " class="paragraph_style_1"><span style="font-size: 14px; " class="Bullet">3.</span><span style="width: 4px; " class="inline-block"></span>The same can be checked in the pricer by following fields <br /></p>
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


