            <div id="id3" style="height: 168px; left: 168px; position: absolute; top: 503px; width: 513px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_1 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_513_168" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <ol>
                    <li style="line-height: 20px; padding-left: 13px; text-indent: -13px; " class="full-width" value="1">
                      <p style="padding-top: 0pt; text-indent: -13px; " class="paragraph_style_3"><span style="font-size: 14px; " class="Bullet">1.</span><span style="width: 2px; " class="inline-block"></span>Time to maturity = 0.07<br /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li style="line-height: 20px; padding-left: 13px; text-indent: -13px; " class="full-width" value="2">
                      <p style="text-indent: -13px; " class="paragraph_style_3"><span style="font-size: 14px; " class="Bullet">2.</span><span style="width: 2px; " class="inline-block"></span>Coupons = 57,52<br /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li style="line-height: 20px; padding-left: 13px; text-indent: -13px; " class="full-width" value="3">
                      <p style="text-indent: -13px; " class="paragraph_style_3"><span style="font-size: 14px; " class="Bullet">3.</span><span style="width: 2px; " class="inline-block"></span>Coupon time in years = 0.07,0.03<br /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li style="line-height: 20px; padding-left: 13px; text-indent: -13px; " class="full-width" value="4">
                      <p style="text-indent: -13px; " class="paragraph_style_3"><span style="font-size: 14px; " class="Bullet">4.</span><span style="width: 2px; " class="inline-block"></span>Final Barrier = 110<br /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li style="line-height: 20px; padding-left: 13px; text-indent: -13px; " class="full-width" value="5">
                      <p style="text-indent: -13px; " class="paragraph_style_3"><span style="font-size: 14px; " class="Bullet">5.</span><span style="width: 2px; " class="inline-block"></span>Change graph setting to “GraphWStock” or “DeltaWStock” or “Price” for different graphs<br /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li style="line-height: 20px; padding-left: 13px; text-indent: -13px; " class="full-width" value="6">
                      <p style="text-indent: -13px; " class="paragraph_style_3"><span style="font-size: 14px; " class="Bullet">6.</span><span style="width: 2px; " class="inline-block"></span>Do refresh graph to change the graph only and not the price grid. <br /></p>
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div id="id4" style="height: 188px; left: 175px; position: absolute; top: 705px; width: 717px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_1 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_717_188" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <ol>
                    <li style="line-height: 20px; padding-left: 13px; text-indent: -13px; " class="full-width" value="1">
                      <p style="padding-top: 0pt; text-indent: -13px; " class="paragraph_style_3"><span style="font-size: 14px; " class="Bullet">1.</span><span style="width: 2px; " class="inline-block"></span>Introducing Time Effect<br /></p>
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                  <p class="paragraph_style"><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style">If you draw the delta / gamma graphs from above theory for 1 day expiration you will get a peaked normal distribution type shape for delta and a two humped normal distribution for gamma. So positive peaked normal for below 110 and negative peaked normal above 110 for gamma. What if time to expiry is &gt; 1 day or, 1 year? The shape is similar but it expands around the barrier (110 in our case). Same can be checked in the pricer by increasing the time to maturity. <br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style"><br /></p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div id="id5" style="height: 312px; left: 122px; position: absolute; top: 929px; width: 829px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_1 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_829_312" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <ol>
                    <li style="line-height: 19px; padding-left: 13px; text-indent: -13px; " class="full-width" value="2">
                      <p style="padding-top: 0pt; text-indent: -13px; " class="paragraph_style_4"><span style="font-size: 13px; " class="Bullet">2.</span><span style="width: 3px; " class="inline-block"></span>Introducing Volatility<br /></p>
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_5"><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_5">Rather than mathematical definition, consider volatility as movement from either side from current spot. This crude version is enough for understanding the structure. Vega is defined as change in price due to change in volatility. Again let’s understand the behavior 1 day before expiry and spot is at or hovering around 109. If volatility is high, there is very high probability that stock cross the barrier or reach much below the barrier. Volatility generally has a smoothing effect on any curve. So if there is convex behavior then volatility will smoothen it out. This is also easy to understand intuitively<br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_5"><br /></p>
                  <ol>
                    <li style="line-height: 19px; padding-left: 13px; text-indent: -13px; " class="full-width" value="1">
                      <p style="text-indent: -13px; " class="paragraph_style_6"><span style="font-size: 13px; " class="Bullet">a)</span><span style="width: 3px; " class="inline-block"></span>If volatility is low then there is a high probability that spot will be at 111 and 108 and in between these values<br /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li style="line-height: 19px; padding-left: 13px; text-indent: -13px; " class="full-width" value="2">
                      <p style="text-indent: -13px; " class="paragraph_style_6"><span style="font-size: 13px; " class="Bullet">b)</span><span style="width: 2px; " class="inline-block"></span>If volatility is high then there is high probability that spot will be at 105 or 115<br /></p>
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_7"><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_7">Problem with case a) is that you will end up rebalancing the delta in positive and negative zones - remember gamma changes sign before expiry so it will cause problems. In short gamma you might end up making losses and in long gamma profits might not be that much high. In long gamma trader is hoping for big moves to make profit. So low volatility causes this gamma bleeding. <br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_7"><br /></p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div style="height: 100px; width: 112px;  height: 100px; left: 45px; position: absolute; top: 729px; width: 112px; z-index: 1; " class="tinyText">
              <div style="position: relative; width: 112px; ">
                <img src="Autocalls_files/shapeimage_2.png" alt="" style="height: 100px; left: 0px; position: absolute; top: 0px; width: 112px; " />
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div style="height: 100px; width: 100px;  height: 100px; left: 14px; position: absolute; top: 1024px; width: 100px; z-index: 1; " class="tinyText">
              <div style="position: relative; width: 100px; ">
                <img src="Autocalls_files/shapeimage_3.png" alt="" style="height: 100px; left: 0px; position: absolute; top: 0px; width: 100px; " />
